*****
[2] Cholera - Kenya (Nairobi)
Date: Thu 5 May 2022
Source: Nation, Kenya Edition [edited]
https://nation.africa/kenya/counties/nairobi/cholera-outbreak-hits-motherland-in-eastleigh-3805742


The Ministry of Health has confirmed a cholera outbreak in Motherland, an informal settlement, in Eastleigh's Section Three area. Health CS Mutahi Kagwe confirmed the outbreak on [Thu 5 May 2022] when flagging off vehicles to support vaccine service delivery for 20 counties. The Director of Public Health in the ministry Dr. Fransic Kuria said his team had already collected samples from the area which are being analyzed.

A total of 2 people have died while 9 more including children have been admitted to in various hospitals within Nairobi following the outbreak of cholera-like symptoms in Kamukunji, Nairobi. According to community health workers at the area, 1 man died at Mama Lucy Kibaki Hospital while the 2nd succumbed while waiting for an ambulance.

In the area, there was open sewage flowing downstream to a dumbing site near the homesteads. The drinking water pipes in the area were submerged in the open raw sewage.

[Byline: Amina Wako]

--
