[3] Cholera - Cameroon
Date: Wed 4 May 2022
Source: Vax Before Travel [edited]
https://www.vaxbeforetravel.com/2022/05/04/cameroons-cholera-outbreak-intensives


The USA CDC recently announced there is an outbreak of cholera in Cameroon's Centre, Littoral, South, Southwest, and North regions.

To prevent cholera, people should follow safe food and water guidelines and wash their hands frequently.

The CDC issued a Watch - Level 1, Practice Usual Precautions, to alert potential visitors to these Cameroon regions. Vaccination against cholera is not routinely recommended because most travelers do not visit areas of active transmission. Travelers (including children) planning to visit regions with active cholera transmission should discuss getting vaccinated with their doctor or pharmacist at least 1 month before travel.

The Vaxchora oral vaccine is FDA authorized in the USA for active immunization against the disease caused by _Vibrio cholerae_ serogroup O1. Vaxchorea is approved for use in adults 18 through 64 years of age traveling to cholera-affected areas.

[Byline: Don Ward Hackett]
