[5] Cholera - Somalia
Date: Fri 6 May 2022
Source: Government of Somalia [edited]
https://reliefweb.int/report/somalia/weekly-acute-watery-diarrhea-situation-report-epidemiological-week-16-18th-24th-april


Weekly Acute Watery Diarrhea Situation Report - Epidemiological Week 16 [18 to 24 Apr 2022]
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Key highlights
--------------
- A total of 652 new suspected AWD/cholera cases (321 female and 331 male) and 3 deaths were reported during week 16.
- Out of 406 (62.27%) were children under 5 years of age.
- The 652 new suspected AWD/cholera cases were reported from districts in the Southwest and Hirshabelle states and Banadir region.
- In week 16 [w/e 24 Apr 2022], the overall attack rate of 79 cases per 100 000 persons were reported from 23 district and the most affected districts include Daynile, Dharkeynley, Wadajir, Baidoa, Afgoye and Jowhar.

